1
00:00:45,439 --> 00:00:46,520
Is it this knife?

2
00:00:51,520 --> 00:00:51,880
Useless.

3
00:00:52,880 --> 00:00:53,240
Drag him out.

4
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:03,640
What are you staring at?

5
00:01:04,359 --> 00:01:04,719
Get out.

6
00:01:07,760 --> 00:01:08,719
Quick, grab some meat.

7
00:01:08,959 --> 00:01:09,319
Hurry, grab it.

8
00:01:09,719 --> 00:01:10,359
Let's go, Dongsheng.

9
00:01:18,239 --> 00:01:19,159
I'll grab a couple bites.

10
00:01:19,400 --> 00:01:20,040
Come here.

11
00:01:21,760 --> 00:01:22,959
Why does your food taste so awful?

12
00:01:24,879 --> 00:01:26,079
It wasn't like this before.

13
00:01:26,280 --> 00:01:27,879
This is worse than temple offerings.

14
00:01:29,400 --> 00:01:30,400
You've eaten temple offerings?

15
00:01:31,480 --> 00:01:32,079
When I was little.

16
00:01:32,359 --> 00:01:32,760
I was naughty.

17
00:01:37,359 --> 00:01:37,640
What's wrong?

18
00:01:37,640 --> 00:01:38,239
My stomach hurts.

19
00:01:38,280 --> 00:01:39,079
I'm hitting the latrine.

20
00:01:41,640 --> 00:01:42,840
Something's off with the food today.

21
00:01:43,799 --> 00:01:44,239
What's going on?

22
00:01:52,319 --> 00:01:53,239
Big Ladle!

23
00:01:53,719 --> 00:01:54,159
Company Commander.

24
00:01:55,239 --> 00:01:56,239
You trying to kill the men?

25
00:01:56,359 --> 00:01:56,599
I...

26
00:01:56,879 --> 00:01:57,280
What's wrong?

27
00:01:58,159 --> 00:01:59,400
What the hell do you think?

28
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:01,040
Look at the food you cooked!

29
00:02:01,280 --> 00:02:02,599
The whole company's got the runs.

30
00:02:03,239 --> 00:02:03,560
That's it.

31
00:02:03,680 --> 00:02:04,400
I'm gonna shoot you dead.

32
00:02:04,640 --> 00:02:05,120
Company Commander,

33
00:02:05,840 --> 00:02:06,120
I...

34
00:02:06,480 --> 00:02:07,239
I didn't cook.

35
00:02:07,640 --> 00:02:08,800
I've been back in town for days.

36
00:02:09,039 --> 00:02:10,240
You're the one who gave me leave.

37
00:02:13,240 --> 00:02:13,599
Oh, right.

38
00:02:14,800 --> 00:02:15,919
How could I forget that?

39
00:02:18,840 --> 00:02:19,960
Then who the hell cooked this?

40
00:02:31,159 --> 00:02:31,560
Company Commander,

41
00:02:31,840 --> 00:02:33,039
this is food for the dead!

42
00:02:34,759 --> 00:02:35,680
Good thing you didn't eat any.

43
00:02:36,080 --> 00:02:36,520
I'm gonna puke.

44
00:02:44,159 --> 00:02:44,960
From today on,

45
00:02:45,599 --> 00:02:46,719
no one is allowed to enter

46
00:02:46,719 --> 00:02:47,719
this kitchen.

47
00:02:49,680 --> 00:02:50,360
But Company Commander,

48
00:02:50,960 --> 00:02:51,960
what about all hundred-plus brothers?

49
00:02:51,960 --> 00:02:52,759
How will they eat?

50
00:02:53,960 --> 00:02:54,759
Find a restaurant.

51
00:02:55,240 --> 00:02:55,719
We'll set up

52
00:02:56,319 --> 00:02:57,240
a regular meal contract.

53
00:02:58,240 --> 00:02:59,280
Yes, yes, yes.

54
00:03:02,439 --> 00:03:03,039
Sirs,

55
00:03:03,319 --> 00:03:04,199
whatever you want tomorrow,

56
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:05,400
just let me know.

57
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:06,479
You got it.

58
00:03:07,280 --> 00:03:08,000
Take care now, gentlemen.

59
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:08,759
Let's go.

60
00:03:11,080 --> 00:03:11,680
Dongsheng.

61
00:03:12,639 --> 00:03:13,280
Dongsheng.

62
00:03:13,919 --> 00:03:14,919
Soldiers these days

63
00:03:14,919 --> 00:03:16,199
eat this well now?

64
00:03:16,439 --> 00:03:17,800
This is practically a banquet.

65
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:18,840
You two...

66
00:03:18,919 --> 00:03:19,680
You two have no idea.

67
00:03:20,080 --> 00:03:20,840
About what?

68
00:03:21,520 --> 00:03:22,199
Stop keeping us in suspense.

69
00:03:22,319 --> 00:03:22,879
Just spit it out.

70
00:03:23,759 --> 00:03:24,560
Let me tell you,

71
00:03:24,879 --> 00:03:25,599
the kitchen at the barracks,

72
00:03:25,599 --> 00:03:26,439
it's haunted.

73
00:03:28,319 --> 00:03:29,080
Haunted?

74
00:03:29,439 --> 00:03:30,199
Haunted how?

75
00:03:30,639 --> 00:03:31,240
I heard that

76
00:03:31,599 --> 00:03:32,879
in the kitchen at midnight,

77
00:03:33,080 --> 00:03:33,840
ghosts slice meat,

78
00:03:33,919 --> 00:03:34,840
ghosts work the wok.

79
00:03:35,199 --> 00:03:35,759
And what's more,

80
00:03:35,919 --> 00:03:37,400
some soldiers ate the ghost food

81
00:03:37,479 --> 00:03:38,560
and got the runs something awful.

82
00:03:39,159 --> 00:03:39,879
And one soldier

83
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:41,000
got scared out of his wits.

84
00:03:41,280 --> 00:03:42,599
That doesn't make sense though.

85
00:03:42,879 --> 00:03:43,680
The barracks

86
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:44,919
are full of strapping young men.

87
00:03:48,199 --> 00:03:49,080
This food really hits the spot.

88
00:03:49,479 --> 00:03:50,039
Now that's the right flavor.

89
00:03:50,039 --> 00:03:50,560
That's the stuff.

90
00:03:56,240 --> 00:03:57,039
This is what they mean by

91
00:03:57,400 --> 00:03:59,000
fortune leaning on misfortune,

92
00:03:59,159 --> 00:04:00,840
misfortune hiding fortune within.

93
00:04:02,080 --> 00:04:02,639
Hurry up and eat.

94
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:04,479
Don't gloat over a good deal.

95
00:04:07,599 --> 00:04:08,000
Sir!

96
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:09,080
Two people are at the gate.

97
00:04:09,759 --> 00:04:10,520
Take me to see them.

98
00:04:10,680 --> 00:04:11,039
Yes, sir.

99
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:23,240
Look there.

100
00:04:23,480 --> 00:04:24,160
Our old friends are here.

101
00:04:26,680 --> 00:04:28,120
What, them again?

102
00:04:28,519 --> 00:04:29,040
You're being...

103
00:04:31,759 --> 00:04:32,240
so stingy.

104
00:04:32,240 --> 00:04:32,879
There's plenty in the pot.

105
00:04:32,879 --> 00:04:33,800
You're eating mine.

106
00:04:37,680 --> 00:04:38,000
Hey, don't!

107
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:38,879
You took it, now I've got none.

108
00:04:38,879 --> 00:04:39,519
I'll get you another one.

109
00:04:40,319 --> 00:04:42,959
Liu Bowen surveyed the feng shui ground,

110
00:04:42,959 --> 00:04:45,360
Zhuge Liang built the Eight-Treasure Altar.

111
00:04:45,360 --> 00:04:46,920
A thousand armies dared not sit there,

112
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:48,839
I beseech the Old Immortal to be seated.

113
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:52,399
The Old Immortal endured great toil on the way,

114
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:54,240
Suffering hardship on the saddle bridge.

115
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:55,680
The main road has wagon tracks,

116
00:04:55,680 --> 00:04:57,240
The small path is heavy with dew.

117
00:04:57,560 --> 00:04:59,120
Wild grass covers the desolate fields,

118
00:04:59,160 --> 00:05:01,319
Old Immortal, please ponder upon arrival.

119
00:05:01,319 --> 00:05:02,720
Many scattered souls roam about,

120
00:05:02,720 --> 00:05:04,399
A bump or knock would be dreadful.

121
00:05:04,399 --> 00:05:06,600
Bumping a gentleman is easy to settle,

122
00:05:06,600 --> 00:05:08,480
But fear striking a petty man,

123
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:11,720
Inviting quarrels and strife.

124
00:05:14,680 --> 00:05:17,680
This little hall measures one zhang three,

125
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:20,480
Queen Mother of the West's royal kitchen.

126
00:05:20,480 --> 00:05:22,079
Fried, sauteed, the dishes smell sweet,

127
00:05:22,079 --> 00:05:24,879
The Queen Mother of the West grows plump.

128
00:05:25,519 --> 00:05:27,319
But fortune turns without warning,

129
00:05:27,319 --> 00:05:29,240
A great cockroach scurried inside.

130
00:05:29,240 --> 00:05:31,759
The Queen Mother of the West felt sick,

131
00:05:32,399 --> 00:05:35,560
Bestowed it on King Yama as a kitchen.

132
00:05:35,560 --> 00:05:37,959
At midnight, ghosts and spirits rise,

133
00:05:37,959 --> 00:05:40,920
The Underworld now has its own canteen.

134
00:05:53,360 --> 00:05:54,600
You sure have a way with words.

135
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:55,399
Just rolls right off your tongue.

136
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:02,000
I get it, I get it.

137
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:03,000
Our Sorceress says,

138
00:06:03,160 --> 00:06:03,879
Right now,

139
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:05,040
this little mess hall of yours

140
00:06:05,240 --> 00:06:07,040
has been requisitioned by the Underworld.

141
00:06:07,560 --> 00:06:08,759
Well, if they've taken it,

142
00:06:09,639 --> 00:06:11,240
then where are my brothers

143
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:12,480
supposed to eat?

144
00:06:17,279 --> 00:06:18,240
I get it, I get it.

145
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:19,560
Our Sorceress says,

146
00:06:20,360 --> 00:06:22,000
As long as she goes to the Underworld

147
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:23,279
and has a chat with King Yama,

148
00:06:23,399 --> 00:06:24,279
King Yama will surely

149
00:06:24,279 --> 00:06:25,079
show her some respect.

150
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:27,519
Out with it.

151
00:06:28,279 --> 00:06:28,839
How much?

152
00:06:29,720 --> 00:06:30,199
You...

153
00:06:30,639 --> 00:06:32,079
Listen to you talk, Sirs.

154
00:06:32,319 --> 00:06:35,199
As if we're the ones taking the money.

155
00:06:35,519 --> 00:06:36,680
This money is all going

156
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:37,360
to the Underworld,

157
00:06:37,600 --> 00:06:39,120
to bribe them for your private kitchen.

158
00:06:39,120 --> 00:06:39,560
Right?

159
00:06:39,639 --> 00:06:40,279
Think about how many there are:

160
00:06:40,399 --> 00:06:41,519
Ox-Head and Horse-Face,

161
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:42,639
Meng Po,

162
00:06:42,680 --> 00:06:43,519
Black and White Impermanence.

163
00:06:43,600 --> 00:06:44,800
Silver's needed everywhere.

164
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:45,639
Everyone has to be paid off.

165
00:06:45,639 --> 00:06:46,120
Am I right?

166
00:06:47,560 --> 00:06:48,079
Fine.

167
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:49,720
You two,

168
00:06:50,160 --> 00:06:51,519
go tear down those wooden boards.

169
00:06:51,759 --> 00:06:52,399
Yes, sir.

170
00:06:56,160 --> 00:06:56,959
Sirs!

171
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:58,959
Why'd you lock us in here?

172
00:06:59,240 --> 00:07:00,399
Let us out!

173
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:02,360
If by tomorrow

174
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:03,439
you're still safe and sound,

175
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:05,560
whatever you ask for,

176
00:07:05,959 --> 00:07:07,079
I'll pay it.

177
00:07:07,279 --> 00:07:08,079
Wait, no...

178
00:07:08,079 --> 00:07:09,360
Let me out!

179
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:10,160
Dismissed.

180
00:07:10,399 --> 00:07:11,519
What are you doing?

181
00:07:11,720 --> 00:07:13,399
Don't you still need us

182
00:07:13,480 --> 00:07:14,639
to get you that private kitchen?

183
00:07:14,680 --> 00:07:15,639
Let us out!

184
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:18,879
You two, don't go either.

185
00:07:22,480 --> 00:07:23,240
What are you staring at?

186
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:24,560
What are you staring at?

187
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:26,600
Maybe I'm just seeing things.

188
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:28,759
So young

189
00:07:28,759 --> 00:07:29,480
and already seeing things?

190
00:07:29,639 --> 00:07:30,560
I'll smack you!

191
00:07:31,120 --> 00:07:31,800
Let's go, let's go.

192
00:07:38,079 --> 00:07:38,639
Dongsheng.

193
00:07:40,319 --> 00:07:41,199
Do you think in this world

194
00:07:41,199 --> 00:07:41,920
ghosts really exist?

195
00:07:45,040 --> 00:07:46,560
I asked my master that question.

196
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:48,879
My master said,

197
00:07:49,199 --> 00:07:50,240
"Ghosts crowd the road to the afterlife,

198
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:51,879
yet not one ghost ever harms a soul.

199
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:54,439
The world is full of people,

200
00:07:54,759 --> 00:07:55,879
yet everyone has a ghost in their heart."

201
00:08:00,399 --> 00:08:01,839
Your master makes a lot of sense.

202
00:08:05,439 --> 00:08:06,399
You miss your master.

203
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:09,399
Get some sleep.

204
00:08:30,920 --> 00:08:32,159
You two, go in and check.

205
00:08:43,840 --> 00:08:44,399
Useless.

206
00:08:54,240 --> 00:08:54,879
You two,

207
00:08:56,159 --> 00:08:56,759
come inside with me and look.

208
00:08:57,080 --> 00:08:57,639
Yes, sir.

209
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:12,919
A ghost turning the millstone!

210
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:30,799
Company Commander, look!

211
00:09:36,360 --> 00:09:37,000
You two, don't move.

212
00:09:37,360 --> 00:09:38,000
I'll go check it out.

213
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:50,519
Out of the way.

214
00:10:29,480 --> 00:10:30,080
It's right here.

215
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:35,039
A fried dough stick.
